How is this different for disadvantaged/vulnerable children?

Please select characteristic of interest and press Go

Children with Special Educational Needs (SEN)

Children with SEN defined as those receiving support from a teaching assistant/SENCO or those enrolled in a special school

Children living with relatives other than their parents (in kinship care)

Children in kinship care defined as those living with relatives other than their parents

Children in care or with a social worker

Children with a social worker defined as those reporting receiving support from a social worker. Those in care defined by those reporting living with foster parents, in a children’s home (secure and non-secure) or those in independent or semi-independent accommodation supported by the local council

Children with a social worker only

Children in care only

Children receiving mental health support

Children currently receiving mental health support

Children receiving mental health support are defined as those reporting receiving support from a counsellor therapist or other health care worker and those reporting living in a mental health hospital

Children in mental health hospitals

Children in mental health hospitals defined as those reporting living in a mental health hospital

Young carers

Young carers defined as children reporting receiving support from a young carers’ project
